@ENDNODE

@NODE Requirements "Requirements"

- AmigaOS 2.04

- SmartFilesystem

- A wonderful Amiga ;)

@ENDNODE


@NODE Usage "Usage"

SFSobject has the following template:

FILE/A,SHOW=UNHIDE/S,HIDE/S,DELETEABLE=DELABLE/S,UNDELETEABLE=UNDELABLE/S:

@{b}FILE@{ub}

The file or directory the be changed. Must be given.

@{b}SHOW@{ub}

The object should be unhidden.

@{b}HIDE@{ub}

The object should be hidden. SFS will not return information on it to
AmigaDOS. But you can access it by directly typing its name. It just won't
appear in directory listings anymore.

@{b}DELABLE@{ub}

The object should be deleteable.

@{b}UNDELABLE@{ub}

The object should be undeleteable. When trying to delete such an object
SFS will return "object is in use" to AmigaDOS. Even when the object is
not delete protected you can't delete the object then.


Of cause SHOW and HIDE, DELABLE and UNDELABLE are mutually exclusive.

@ENDNODE

