revision 1.6
date: 2002/03/23 18:19:33;  author: Helios;  state: Exp;  lines: +3 -3
- using exit() instead of returning, since something in stormgcc
  startup code seems to be pretty broken: does not return a value
  to AmigaDOS at all

revision 1.5
date: 2002/03/23 17:34:20;  author: Helios;  state: Exp;  lines: +26 -15
- now compiled with StormGCC
- not longer residentable, did moan about 32 bit references in amiga.lib
  and I did not found one for residentable programs, so I just left this
  out for now. Shouldn't be a big problem and you have the source and
  can fix it yourself ;-) ...
- ... cause SFSobject is licensed under GPL now
- now returns proper error codes to the shell on all errors (untested)

revision 1.4
date: 1999/10/14 23:23:35;  author: helios;  state: Exp;  lines: +3 -5
- adapted to StormC V4 beta. It found a missing ";". StormC 3
  didn't moan about it.
- recompiled with StormC V4. Saved 44 byte. Does it use a
  smaller startup code? ;-)
- added proper include path for SFS stuff and removed
  superfluos #include's
- StormC V4 still does not parse nested comments correctly.

revision 1.3
