revision 1.2
date: 1999/10/12 21:58:12;  author: helios;  state: Exp;  lines: +98 -79
- first beta release
- replaced my bloated recycled dir code that does not really
  work even after changing the wrong BADDR() to MKBADDR()
  when trying to convert rlock to rlockbtr by some genius
  code by J—rg Strohmayer. Many thanks, J—rg.
- thus recycled dir checking now works.
- added checking for mutually exclusive options.
- SFSobject should be quite safe now.
- TODO: Querying OBJECTBITS to allow really good option
  handling. Currently HIDE option alone would also
